The paper deals with the task of automatically finding missing words in a video's incomplete textural description, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method that employs merging LSTMs, which is a deep learning technique, indicating that it could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves inferencing missing words, which is a task related to natural language understanding (NLU), suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with videos, which is a multimedia format, indicating that it could also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
